{
  "texts": [
    "For one thing, fulfilling our duties of attention can be constitutive of our morally significant roles and relationships.",
    "This is most apparent where further consequences are held constant.",
    "If you're babysitting and you spend the whole time staring at your phone, paying no attention to the child in your charge, this makes you a negligent caregiver.",
    "If it turns out that she tucked herself into bed and went to sleep as soon as her parents left, then your outward behavior and its consequences may be no different than if you were paying attention to her.",
    "The moral difference, then, between negligence and responsibility here is evidently just a difference in attention allocation."
  ]
}